Pandas is a Python library used to work with data in table format (like Excel or database tables).

ğŸ‘‰ In simple words:
Pandas = Tool to read, clean, analyze, and manipulate data easily in Python

ğŸ“Œ What is Pandas?

Pandas is an open-source Python library for data manipulation and analysis.
It helps you:
--Load data (CSV, Excel, SQL)
--Clean data
--Transform data
--Analyze data
--Prepare data for ML or reports
It mainly works using tables called DataFrames.

ğŸ§  Why Pandas is Used (Main Reasons)
1ï¸âƒ£ Easy to Work With Table Data
Pandas provides special structures:
Series â†’ Single column
DataFrame â†’ Full table (rows + columns)

2ï¸âƒ£ Helps Clean Messy Data
Pandas can:
--Remove duplicates
--Fill missing values
--Replace wrong data
--Convert data types

3ï¸âƒ£ Very Useful for Analysis
You can easily calculate:
Mean
Sum
Count
Median
Group data using groupby()

4ï¸âƒ£ Works With Other Data Tools
Pandas works well with:
NumPy â†’ math operations
Matplotlib â†’ graphs
Scikit-learn â†’ machine learning

ğŸ“Œ Core Concept: DataFrame (Most Important)

A DataFrame is:
--2D table
--Different column data types allowed
--Similar to SQL table or Excel sheet
Example:
Name	Age	  Salary

ğŸ“Œ What We Do Using Pandas (Main Tasks)
ğŸ”¹ Load Data
import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_csv("data.csv")

ğŸ”¹ Check Data
df.head()
df.info()
df.describe()

ğŸ”¹ Clean Data
df.dropna()
df.fillna(0)
df.drop_duplicates()

ğŸ”¹ Filter Data
df[df["age"] > 25]

ğŸ”¹ Group Data
df.groupby("city")["salary"].mean()

ğŸ§¾ One Line Summary
ğŸ‘‰ Pandas is used to load, clean, transform, and analyze table data easily in Python.


